The third edition of Vivacity PR annual Glocalisation and Branding Summit will hold today at the NEPC Building, Maitama, Abuja. With the theme: ‘A Synergy between Global and Local Strategies’, this edition of the summit aims to deepen knowledge and further discussions on glocalisation processes for all Nigerian SMEs. The founder Vivacity PR and convener, Oluwakemi Ann-Melody Areola, said the essence of the summit targets MSMEs, intrapreneurs, entrepreneurs and multinational organisations with the aim of creating strong and sustainable business alliances across a number of key sectors — ICT, PR, Fashion, Cosmetics, Automobile, Art, Law, Finance, Culture & Tourism, Retail, Hotel & Hospitality, Education, Mining, Renewable Energy, Infrastructural Development, Real Estate, Health, and more. 